spans.text: thou who all my Soul inspires
my soft Complainings to his Ear
my soft Complainings to his Ear
What Odours do these opening Buds exhale
with a borrowed Grace , And Roses blush to emulate thy Face
Die Match the bright Azure of thy shining Eye
Die Match the bright Azure of thy shining Eye
a grateful Shade , And brighter Colours
thee the Cedars form a grateful Shade , And brighter Colours paint the enamelled Mead : O !
For thee the Cedars form a grateful Shade , And brighter Colours paint the enamelled Mead : O !
each winding Mead , And follow where thy charming Footsteps

Yet let me view thee ; on that lovely Face Let me with fond ecstatic Rapture gaze ; Let thy Voice charm me with its Magic Sound , And my fond Soul with thrilling Pleasure wound ; For sweet's thy Beauties to my ravished Sight , And thy dear Voice my listening Ears delight
thy Voice charm me with its Magic Sound
on that lovely Face Let me with fond ecstatic Rapture gaze
that Couch , with Nature's Bounties spread , At Ease reclined
What Beauties in that smiling Form appear ; How soft , how mild , how more than heavenly fair
The Sun with less refulgent Brightness gleams
me , Heaven , the fleeting Breath you gave , For Love's as strong as Death , and powerful as the Grave
